The South African government is attempting to repatriate citizens in foreign countries wanting to return home. eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways has agreed to provide repatriation charter flights to various international destinations. This follows high-level discussions with various embassies and relevant government departments. READ: SAA cancels flights amid coronavirus pandemic The first of these flights is expected to leave the country on Friday, ferrying German citizens. Flights will leave Johannesburg and Cape Town for Munich and Frankfurt. SAA's business rescue practitioners say negotiations are ongoing with other governments to repatriate their citizens. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.